content: It is nice to see you all here.
In less than 1 month, the World Championship will begin.
I hope to see you all there, face to face. :)
The only problem is money, haha
It is most wonderful renju event, where people can see all the masters face to face, speak to them, play with them, study with them, etc
If anyone of you wants to go, you can visit http://www.renju.ee/wc website,
and find all the information about how to travel
Last week, we learned about how to prepare for QT (qualification tournament).
The goal was to get among top 5.
Now, imagine you are in AT now, what place would you want to get there?

Aurora, Ikon, hobbang, Whiz, slamduk, coco_yuang, akira, Samsone, Iskander, hui, ouyang, cloud, Yue, tommy, shan, chess, tianxia, paradise, sosei, voshkod, dreamy, findfind, Liuchao, yun_shou, mima, roger8961, Yeats, hallo, YKS, ANNITA, blueice, ErkiN, slaty, shuwang, weigui, nu723, ethereal, Lithium, rosebud, danfengyue, dogswang, wawa, Zelerny.
AT - the final of world championship
There are 12 players in AT, world's best players,
so it means you will have 11 tough games
How many points do you need, to get 1st place?
the points 10 and 11 were too high.
For Sushkov 4 years ago it was not enough
yue, 1989 there was old system, only 10 players
you can give up 2 points only
if you want to get 9 points,
then you need to prepare against every opponent

Yulia Savrasova (Russia) 7 dan
Sergey Artemiev (Russia)
Konstantin Chingin (Russia)
Hiroshi Okabe (Japan), 7 dan
Tunnet Taimla (Estonia), 6 dan
Ando Meritee (Estonia), 9 dan
Hannes Hermansson (Sweden), 4 dan
and the rest of the 5 people (including you), will be decided 1 day before WC
As you may notice, this year's WC players are very young.
Among these 7 people, i am oldest
and you're the most high rank
For the first time in WC history, a female player got AT seat.
What do you know about her?
She is young girl, but current Russian Champion
before, she has played in Women World Championship - WT.
She won WT when she was 12 years old!
one of the best player in Russia
Of course, WT is much weaker than AT.
Likely, nearly all of you could be in top 3 in WT
it's impolite to ask about a lady's age
especially our lovely female students from China
whom we will prepare for AT win?
then we will do it more boring way
we can only study opponent's weakness,
but cannot map it with our strength
For example, when I prepare for games,
I think of my strong sides, and opponent's weak sides,
perhasp, most students don't understand your idea?
we needed a volunteer to simulate the participation in AT.
and what is your strong point?
only that way, the lesson can have very realistic idea
u means a student play with u ?
Maybe I can have a try?
then you should understand the idea
I will try if only my English is better...
this is my first time to be here.
We imagine, hobbang did a good job in QT, got among top 5.
and now he is going to AT.
most students don't ahev database. i think.
Where can we find the database?
If you want to become serious player, the database is important.
You can make database by yourself.
you all use Renlib anyway for homework
every time when World Championship or other tournament ends,
the organizers usually publish finished games
and put together, to make one large database
renlib has easy function, to merge data files
I will do it after WC:)
i help to check what Savrasova plays
she doesnt play safe or positional way
her calculation does not seem to be too good,
but she is dangerous by choosing very difficult variants
hehe, maybe ando's renlib is bigest in world
2 years ago, this position was her favorite gambling variant.
Hobbang, do you know how to play as black?
i think this 12 was her favorite idea
sorry i could not be in time, to become champion :P
in AT, the time limit for 1 player is: 2 hours main time + 30 seconds added after each move

your clock time has been added by 5 minutes
if you undo in tournament, you will be disqualified
did you check data files now?
in WC you have no help
all you think is all you get
did you get any help for that move now
because this style is bestman's fovorite weapon
so you took that move from your memory now?
the difference between renju player and lawyer is - lawyer can always check from books, but renju player must carry all in head
if you dont know this variant, you are likely to fail here,
so, even if you didn't know win yet,
because you only need to know that she likes this variant,
and you prepare for her specially
and find win a week before AT
then do you write down somewhere?
i write down my study in lib file
so that some years later, i can recall easily
Now, hobbang, tell us, whats your favorite opening
i though you can remember all :)
what will you play if you have to open the game
she has played only 1 game by this 5th move in the past.
So you can use her weakness
How many of you know this variant? say Me
i think several 16th moves are possible.
Anyway, here is a positional game,
I don't know where is best 16th.. :)
you should be able to win later
if you play with her, you set i11
so what is the correct way for black then?
it is not black win opening
whether advantage becomes trouble, or success
many russians consider him as most talented Russian player
so he will not play soft variants like d11,
because it may easily end with draw.
what kind of gamble he makes from here
i check if database has answer
I learned this style anlysis lesson :)
alicecooper, tactics is - when you can skip 4, then skip 4
since white cannot go j4, so black can skip j4
you play 4 only when see the final
a skipped 4 can always give more chance for attacker
in this variant, it doesnt matter, skip or not
but some variants, its very important
so its better to have such habit
so after 2 games, hobban leads with 2 pts
in 3rd round, you will meet Okabe
he is good at 1 minute game,
if you can play very slowly,
since okabe is HPO in ORC,
you can get thousands of his games from ORC lib
Since there is so much data about Okabe,
we don't need to analyse it here now.
I played him about 50 games in 1 min =)
so you should be able to beat him even by skill.
this year QT has so many strong players,
who failed to get direct place for AT
like Yamaguchi, Iio, Sushkov, Klimashin, Karlsson, etc
so you should worry about these players even more.
After you beat Hermansson, you have 3,5 from 4 games.

But next opponent is Tunnet Taimla
guys, you can help hobbang now
he is student too in this class. he can see this lesson. :)
sure he will download this file after class
so he will read, how he will lose
if you have very strong opponent
then dont try to play risky
a question to all of you
he will swap and play h9
maybe someone pursue I11 studies deeply
(actually we have to help hobbang, not ando :P)
hard to say for each case, but as an overall average
so you can take this probability
but go only there IF you are sure about win
if not, then dont play it
because failing to win gives white big advantage
how about h6? is too risky?
you dont need to make strange moves
just play normal and safe way
its is his job to invent something,
so you should prepare for both cases
i said yes before you ask vcf
if tunnet suspects, that you know such trap moves
vhite has vcf if you play that 19
you can wait with that move maybe
because sometimes e6 is even better point for black
you will surely achieve draw here, at least
you can always go h12 later
you still have enough time to think here
so he must take more risks
just wait for his risky move
so lets say you get draw
and in the good schedule of winning
you can try d11, go into long variant,
and maybe i will do something stupid
while trying hard to win game
It is just an example, of course
but the idea is right - you play with stronger opponent, play such draw variant,
and see how strong player goes crazy
This is your only chance, if you want to win AT.
next time, you cannot win by same tactics
for example Tunnet had better chance last time,
because now many people will think "draw" is enough against Tunnet,
so he must work harder than before
Now, Tunnet will have as difficult AT as me
to get 9 points from 11 against opponents who are all happy with "draw", is very difficult
And now, we can only hope you will come to QT, and make our prepatation come true!
thank you all!! see you in AT! :)))
